UNITED STATES ex rel. NEWMAN v. WALLIS, Immigration Com’r. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. December 15, 1921.) No. 119. Appeal from the District Court of the United States for the Southern District of New! York. Application for writ of habeas corpus by the United States, on the relation of Barol Newman, against Frederick A. Wallis, Commissioner of Immigration of the Port of New York. From an order dismissing the writ, relator appeals. Affirmed. Morris Jablow, of New York City, for appellant. William Hayward, of New York City, for appellee.

Before HOUGH, MAN-TON, and MAYER, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Order affirmed in open court.
